channel.title: Making my RSPS Online
channel.description:
Heyy I used to have my server running non hamachi.. something happened and i needed to get hamachi.. this is really annoying cuz now nobody wants to take the time to download hamachi. I would really sppreciate if someone could explain what this means to me. I recently tryed to make the server online eithout hamachi. I wanna see if the run/cmd ipconfig works to see my ips and all that good stuff. I get this new mssge which I never got before
'ipconfig' is not recognized as an internal or external command, operable program or batch file.
can someone explain to me why its saying this bull shit?! i would really appreciate if someone can help me with Team Viewer.. this is really pissing me off. If someone would take the time and help me get it back online ( non hamachi ) I will make u co owner on my server. I got JDK. Did the port fowarding and got the no-ip client thing that says ur server is online. I feel this is the only thing in the way. and if u do no the answer can u explain it to me in baby steps.. ( lol )

item.title: Making my RSPS Online
item.dc:creator: @dan01941 dan01941
item.description:
@dan01941 wrote:

All you got to do Is Right-Click Cmd And Click Run as Adminstrator

There you go just type in: ipconfig and your ready to go

item.title: Making my RSPS Online
item.dc:creator: @badger41 badger41
item.description:
@badger41 wrote:

runyluny:

I did set my enviorement variables to make my jdk work better is there anything i need to do?

Well, as long as you have environment variables set, you wont be able to use the cmd prompt to use ipconfig, the reason is its trying to use java with your ipconfig command.
Just download the small gui on the microsoft site and it will tell you all your ipds, default gateway etc.
